New Azure administrators often encounter similar challenges during their first production deployments.

Common mistakes include:

* Assigning excessive permissions
* Ignoring resource tagging
* Forgetting backup configuration
* Leaving unused resources running
* Skipping documentation
* Neglecting monitoring
* Exposing management ports publicly

For example, failing to configure monitoring may delay the detection of application failures until users report problems.

A real-life use case is reducing operational incidents by adopting best practices from the beginning of an Azure administration career.

Learning from common mistakes accelerates professional growth.
